atas D.959 & D.960\n|\n|[[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n|479 7588\n|-\n|2018\n|June 2018\n|[[Leonard Bernstein|Bernstein]]: Symphony No. 2 \"The Age of Anxiety\"\n|[[Berliner Philharmonic]]<br>(conducted by Sir [[Simon Rattle]])\n|[[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n|483 5539\n|-\n|}\n\n===Live albums===\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable toccolours\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Date of issue\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Date of recording\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Cover art\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Album details\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Collaborating artists\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Record label\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Catalogue no.\n|-\n|1977\n|\n|\n|[[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Beethoven)|Beethoven: Piano Sonata No. 8, Op. 13 \"Path\u00e9tique\"]]<br>Prokofiev: Piano Sonata No.3, Op.28<br>Bacewicz: Piano Sonata No.2\n|\n|Polskie Nagrania Muza\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|\n|\n|[[Piano Concerto No. 1 (Chopin)|Chopin: Piano Concerto No. 1]] <br> (recorded in 1979)\n|[[Kyrill Kondrashin]] conducting <br> [[Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra]]\n|[[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n|\n|}\n\n===Video releases===\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable toccolours\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Date of issue\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Date of filming\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Video details\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Collaborating artists\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Record label\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Catalogue no.\n|-\n|1984\n|\n|[[Brahms]]: Piano Concerto No. 1\n|[[Leonard Bernstein]] conducting [[Vienna Philharmonic]]\n|[[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n|\n|-\n|1985\n|\n|[[Brahms]]: Piano Concerto No. 2\n|[[Leonard Bernstein]] conducting [[Vienna Philharmonic]]\n|[[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|\n|[[Chopin]]: 4 Ballades; Fantasie; Barcarolle; Scherzo No. 2 / [[Schubert]]: 4 Impromptus Op. 90\n|\n|[[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Polish music]]\n*[[Arthur Rubinstein]]\n*[[International Chopin Piano Competition]]\n*[[List of Poles]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=q61946}}\n* [http://www.deutschegrammophon.com/cat/result?ART_ID=ZIMKR Krystian Zimerman discography]\n* {{Worldcat id|lccn-n81-55115}}\n* {{NYTtopic|people/z/krystian_zimerman}}\n\n{{L\u00e9onie Sonning Music Prize laureates}}\n{{Accademia Musicale Chigiana International Prize laureates}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zimerman, Krystian}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:International Chopin Piano Competition winners]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Zabrze]]\n[[Category:Deutsche Grammophon artists]]\n[[Category:Polish classical pianists]]\n[[Category:Polish music educators]]\n[[Category:Piano pedagogues]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Polish classical pianist}}\n{{distinguish|text=dressage rider [[Christian Zimmermann]]}}\n[[File:Krystian Zimerman 2004.jpg|thumb|Zimerman, backstage at the Seligman Performing Arts Center, November 2004]] \n'''Krystian Zimerman''' (born 5 December 1956) is a Polish pianist and conductor who has been described as one of the finest living pianists.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2009/apr/29/krystian-zimerman-polish-pianist|title=In praise of ... Krystian Zimerman|date=29 April 2009|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=29 April 2009|location=London}}</ref><ref name=RH>{{cite news|last=Swed|first=Mark|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/culturemonster/2009/04/krystian-zimermans-last-us-appearance-at-disney-hall.html|title=Review: Krystian Zimerman's controversial appearance at Disney Hall|date=27 April 2009|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=29 April 2009}}</ref> In 1975, he won the IX [[International Chopin Piano Competition]].\n\n==Biography==\nZimerman was born in [[Zabrze]], [[People's Republic of Poland|Poland]], and studied at the [[Karol Szymanowski Academy of Music]] in [[Katowice]] under [[Andrzej Jasi\u0144ski]]. His international career was launched when he won the 1975 Warsaw [[International Chopin Piano Competition]]. He performed with the [[Berlin Philharmonic]] in 1976, conducted by [[Herbert Blomstedt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.berliner-philharmoniker.de/en/titelgeschichten/2014-2015/blomstedt-thielemann-kavakos/|title=Berliner Philharmoniker Blomstedt-Thielemann-Kavakos|website=Berliner-philharmoniker.de|accessdate=15 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160922154717/https://www.berliner-philharmoniker.de/en/titelgeschichten/2014-2015/blomstedt-thielemann-kavakos/|archive-date=22 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He debuted in the United States with the [[New York Philharmonic]] in 1979. He has toured widely and made a number of recordings. Since 1996, he has taught piano at the [[City of Basel Music Academy|Music Academy]] in [[Basel]], Switzerland. In 1999, Zimerman created the [http://www.polishfestivalorchestra.com/ Polish Festival Orchestra] to commemorate the 150th anniversary of [[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin]]'s death.<ref>{{cite web|author=Culture.pl|url=http://culture.pl/en/artist/krystian-zimerman|title=Krystian Zimerman - Biography &#124; Artist|website=Culture.pl|date=15 October 2015|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nZimerman is best known for his interpretations of [[Romantic music]], but has performed a wide variety of classical pieces and is a supporter of contemporary music. [[Witold Lutos\u0142awski]] wrote his piano concerto for Zimerman, who has recorded it two times. Among his best-known recordings are the [[Piano concerto|concerti]] of [[Piano Concerto (Grieg)|Grieg]] and [[Piano Concerto (Schumann)|Schumann]] with [[Herbert von Karajan]]; the [[Johannes Brahms|Brahms]] concerti with [[Leonard Bernstein]], the piano concerti of [[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin|Chopin]], one recording conducted by [[Carlo Maria Giulini]] and a later one conducted by himself at the keyboard; the Third, Fourth and Fifth Piano Concertos of [[Ludwig van Beethoven|Beethoven]] under Bernstein (Zimerman himself led the [[Vienna Philharmonic]] from the keyboard in Beethoven's First and Second Concertos); the first and second piano concerti of [[Sergei Rachmaninoff|Rachmaninoff]]; the piano concerti of [[Franz Liszt|Liszt]] with [[Seiji Ozawa]], the piano concerti of [[Maurice Ravel|Ravel]] with [[Pierre Boulez]], and solo piano works by Chopin, Liszt, [[Claude Debussy|Debussy]] and [[Franz Schubert|Schubert]]. In 2006, Zimerman recorded Brahms' [[Piano Concerto No. 1 (Brahms)|Piano Concerto No. 1]] with the [[Berlin Philharmonic]] conducted by Sir [[Simon Rattle]] (DG 477 5413; Limited Edition DG 477 6021).\n\nZimerman has collaborated with conductors and artists such as [[Claudio Abbado]], [[Vladimir Ashkenazy]], [[Daniel Barenboim]], [[Leonard Bernstein]], [[Pierre Boulez]], [[Charles Dutoit]], [[Carlo Maria Giulini]], [[Bernard Haitink]], [[Herbert von Karajan]], [[Kirill Kondrashin]], [[Erich Leinsdorf]], [[Lorin Maazel]], [[Zubin Mehta]], [[Riccardo Muti]], [[Seiji Ozawa]], [[Simon Rattle]], [[Esa-Pekka Salonen]], [[Giuseppe Sinopoli]], [[Stanis\u0142aw Skrowaczewski]] or [[Wolfgang Sawallisch]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.polmic.pl/index.php?option=com_mwosoby&id=59&view=czlowiek&litera=29&Itemid=6&lang=pl|title=Krystian Zimerman|access-date=27 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Criticism of US policy==\nOn 26 April 2009 Zimerman vowed to his audience at [[Los Angeles]]'s [[Walt Disney Concert Hall]] that, in protest of America's placement of a [[Poland\u2013Russia relations#Present#Deployment of US missile defense shield in Poland and the South Ossetia War|missile defense shield in Poland]], this would be his final appearance in the United States.<ref name=RH/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ireport.com/docs/DOC-250340|title=Krystian Zimerman, declares US boycott in protest at Disney Hall in Los Angeles|website=Ireport.com|accessdate=29 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100507212452/http://www.ireport.com/docs/DOC-250340|archive-date=7 May 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> He had made a similar comment in 2006, stating he would not return until [[George W. Bush]] was out of office.<ref>{{cite news|first=Andrew|last=Gumbel|title=Classical music and opera Polish pianist stops show with anti-US tirade|date=28 April 2009|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2009/apr/28/krystian-zimerman-missile-defence-poland|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=28 April 2009}}</ref> As of November 2019 he has not made any further appearances in the United States.<ref>[https://www.songkick.com/artists/408477-krystian-zimerman/gigography ''Tour Dates'' (Kristian Zimerman) - accessed 26 November 2019]</ref>\nPart of his disenchantment with the USA may be the increased security at US airports, which makes it difficult to bring his piano into the country. In incidents in 2001 and 2006, one of his Steinway pianos was completely destroyed and another one damaged by security staff at New York's JFK airport.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.today.com/id/30442451#.UngMYb-fd1M|title=Piano great says he won\u2019t return to U.S. - today|website=Today.com|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Andrew Gumbel in Los Angeles |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2009/apr/28/krystian-zimerman-missile-defence-poland |title=Polish pianist stops show with anti-US tirade &#124; Music|newspaper=The Guardian|date=28 April 2009|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://magazin.klassik.com/news/teaser.cfm?ID=10106|title=klassik.com : Pianist Krystian Zimerman unterbricht Konzert wegen Smartphone-Mitschnitt aus dem Publikum|website=Magazin.klassik.com|date=23 October 2015|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/germany/10098301/Pianist-Krystian-Zimerman-storms-out-of-concert-in-protest-at-being-filmed-on-phone.html|location=London|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|first=Jeevan|last=Vasagar|title=Pianist Krystian Zimerman storms out of concert in protest at being filmed on phone|date=4 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesargus.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20061020/NEWS/610200328/1011/FEATURES02|title=Krystian Zimerman speaks|website=Timesargus.com|date=20 October 2006|accessdate=28 October 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725220618/http://www.timesargus.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20061020%2FNEWS%2F610200328%2F1011%2FFEATURES02|archivedate=25 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Krystian Zimerman 2018.jpg|thumb|Zimerman in 2017, Basel|alt=A portrait photography of a man with white hair, moustache and beard, peering over a pair of large sun-glasses]]\nZimerman lives with his wife and two children in [[Binningen, Switzerland|Binningen]], near [[Basel]], Switzerland,<ref>Anthony Tommasini (13 April 1997). [https://www.nytimes.com/1997/04/13/arts/sidestepping-the-celebrity-circuit.html \"Sidestepping The Celebrity Circuit\"]. ''[[The New York Times]]''.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polskamuza.eu/siedemodslon.php?id=162|title=Polska Muza - Siedem Ods\u0142on|website=Polskamuza.eu|accessdate=29 December 2018}}</ref> where he has spent the greater part of his life. He divides his time among family, concerts, and performances of chamber music. When not touring or building pianos, he has been editing piano editions of the works of [[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Szpilman]] for [[Boosey & Hawkes]] and has written a piece on [[aesthetics]], which was published in Poland in March 2005.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}}\n\n==Awards and honours==\n* Voivod-wide Prokofiev Competition (First prize) (1974; [[Katowice]]) \n* [[International Chopin Piano Competition]]  (First prize) (1975; [[Warsaw]])\n* [[Accademia Musicale Chigiana]] Award, (1985; [[Siena]], [[Italy]])\n* [[L\u00e9onie Sonning Music Prize]] (1994; [[Denmark]])\n* [[Honorary doctor]] of the [[Karol Szymanowski Academy of Music]] in [[Katowice]] (2005)\n* [[National Order of the Legion of Honour]] (2005; [[France]])<ref>{{cite news|url=https://culture.pl/en/artist/krystian-zimerman|title=Krystian Zimerman|website=Culture.pl|access-date=8 April 2018}}</ref>\n* Gold [[Medal for Merit to Culture - Gloria Artis]] (2010)\n* [[Commander]]'s Cross with Star of the [[Order of Polonia Restituta]] (2013)\n* [[Diapason d'Or]] (2015; France)\n* [[Honorary doctor]] of the [[Fryderyk Chopin University of Music]] in [[Warsaw]] (2015)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.chopin.edu.pl/pl/2015/10/uroczystosc-inauguracji-roku-akademickiego-20152016|title=UROCZYSTO\u015a\u0106 INAUGURACJI ROKU AKADEMICKIEGO 2015/2016|website=Chopin.edu.pl|access-date=8 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\nMost of Zimerman's recordings have been released by [[Deutsche Grammophon]], with which he has an exclusive lifelong contract.\n\n===Studio albums===\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable toccolours\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Date of issue\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Date of recording\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Album details\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Collaborating artists\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Record label\n! style=\"background:lightyellow; color:black;\"|Catalogue no.\n|-\n|1975\n|\n|[[Piano Concerto No. 1 (Chopin)|Chopin: Piano Concerto No. 1]]\n|Jerzy Maksymiuk conducting<br>[[Polish Radio Symphony Orchestra]]\n|[[Polskie Nagrania Muza]]\n|\n|-\n|1977\n|\n|[[Chopin]]: Andante spianato and Grande Polonaise & other piano works\n|\n|[[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n|2530 826\n|-\n|1978\n|\n|[[Waltzes (Chopin)|Chopin: 14 Waltzes]]\n|\n|[[Deutsche Grammophon]]\n|\n|-\n|1978\n|January 1978\n|[[Mozart]]: Piano Sonatas KV280, 281, 311 & 330\n|\n|[[Deutsch